# Introduction
## Where this repository comes from
This repository is the work from, and for, the cs213 assignment: *"Song Library"*.   
[The course](https://www.cs.rutgers.edu/academics/undergraduate/course-synopses/course-details/01-198-213-software-methodology)
was taken during Spring 2021

---

# REQUIREMENTS
This project uses the JavaFX library to supply the gui.   
To install, and setup the library, I recommend looking at tutorials such as 
[this one](https://openjfx.io/openjfx-docs/#introduction)

Other than that, Java version 17 (and below) should work.

---

# INSTALATION
## Cloning the repository (via terminal)
`git clone https://github.com/AdamFariello/Song-Library` 

## Setting up the project

### Using eclipse
1. [Install eclipse](https://www.eclipse.org/downloads/packages/)

1. Import project into eclipse with smart git import
2. Add arguments for virtual machine:		
"-–module-path –add-modules javafx.controls,javafx.fxml,javafx.media"
> this argument might possible be in the project, if so: then ignore step 3
 
### Other methods
If some other method is required, or just wanted -- 
look into the documentation for installation tips 

# EXECUTION
------------
* Run file src/songlib.java
